AMD RAID Driver for RHEL 7.5/8.2/8.3/8.4 x64


1.Install the AMD-RAID drivers during a RHEL UEFI Linux Installation
	NOTE: Prior to starting this procedure, obtain the AMD-RAID drivers from your system supplier or motherboard vendor. Copy the AMD-RAID drivers to a USB flash drive. See Copy AMD-RAID drivers: Linux.
	NOTE: When installing Red Hat Linux, use the Linux dd installation mode instead of the Linux expert mode.
	NOTE: It is AMD's recommendation that a reset/reboot of the system is performed whenever the user is adding or removing a SATA M.2 SSD or NVMe device(s).
	      In the OS, issue a reset/reboot
	      Wait for the AMD BIOS screen to display, press ESC to enter BIOS.
	      Power off the system.
	      Install or remove the necessary device(s).
  	      Power on the system and allow the OS to boot properly.
	NOTE: Not all of the windows indicated in this procedure will appear during the installation.
	1.	Power-on the system.
	2.	Insert the Red Hat operating system CD-ROM or DVD into the system’s CD or DVD drive.
	3.	Create a bootable array, see Section 3.
	4.	At the Red Hat Enterprise Linux Welcome window
		•	Press the Up Arrow
		•	Select Install Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.5/8.2/8.3  (should be high-lighted in White)
		•	Press E
		•	Press the down arrow to the linuxefi /images string
		•	Press the END key 
			•	Add “inst.dd modprobe.blacklist=ahci modprobe.blacklist=nvme”  to the end of the existing string
			Example – linuxefi /images……..quiet inst.dd modprobe.blacklist=ahci modprobe.blacklist=nvme 
		•	Press CTRL X
		Note: if you no longer get anything on the display after a couple minutes, reset and try again with these settings.
			•	Add “inst.dd modprobe.blacklist=ahci modprobe.blacklist=nvme nomodeset”  to the end of the existing string
			Example – linuxefi /images……..quiet inst.dd modprobe.blacklist=ahci modprobe.blacklist=nvme nomodeset
		•	Press CTRL X
	5.	At the Driver Disk Device Selection
		•	Insert the USB drive (which contains the AMD-RAID drivers) into the USB port
		•	Press 1 – number of the flash drive
		•	Press Enter
	6.	At the Choose Driver Disk ISO file
		•	Press 1 – number of the dd-rcraid-RHEL….el7.x86_64.iso entry
		•	Press Enter
	7.	At the Select Drivers to Install
		•	Press 1 – number of the /media/DD/…..x86_64.rpm entry
		•	Press Enter
		The /media/DD/… is now selected and should look like [X] /media/DD/……x86_64.rpm
		•	Press C
		•	Press Enter
	8.	At the Driver Disk Device Selection 
		•	Press C
		•	Press Enter
		•	Remove the USB drive (which contains the AMD-RAID drivers)
	NOTE: For RHEL 7.5 and RHEL 8.2, perform steps 9 - 12
	9.	At the Welcome to Red Hat Enterprise Linux Screen
		•	Choose the desired Language
		•	Choose the desired Country
		•	In the bottom right corner, Click Continue
	10.	At the Installation Summary Screen
		•	Configure the following:
		•	Under Localization
		•		Date and Time
		•		Keyboard
		•		Language Support
		•	Under Software
		•		Installation Source
		•		Software Selection
		•			Under Base Environments
		•				Select Server with GUI
		•			Under Add-Ons for Selected Environments
		•				Select Compatibility Library
		•		In the upper left corner, Click Done
		•	Under System
		•		Installation Destination 
		•			Under Local Standard Disks
		•				Select AMD-RAID Array
						Select I will configure partitioning
						Click Done
		•	Click the Click here to create them automatically link
				Under Installation
					Select Data /home
					Change file system to ext4
					Select system /boot
					Change file system to ext4
					Select system /rhel-root
					Change file system to ext4
				In the upper left corner, Click Done
				In the Summary of Changes window, Click Accept Changes
		•	Network and Hostname
		•		In the bottom left corner, enter a valid Hostname
		•			Select an Ethernet Port
		•			In the bottom right corner,  Click Configure
		•			Enter valid entries
		•			Click Save
		•		In the upper left corner, Click Done
	11.	In the bottom right corner, Click  Beginning Installation
	NOTE: system may appear to be locked up, please wait patiently, the system is busy writing out files and will respond shortly.
	12.	At the Configuration Window
		•	Click Root Password
		•		Enter an applicable root password
		•		Re-enter the root password
		•	Click User Creation
		•		Enter a Full Name
		•		Enter a Username
		•		Enter an applicable password
		•		Re-enter the user password
		•	In the upper right corner, Click Done
	NOTE: For RHEL 8.3 Peform steps 13 - 17	
	13.	At the Welcome to Red Hat Enterprise Linux Screen
		•	Choose the desired Language
		•	Choose the desired Country
		•	In the bottom right corner, Click Continue
	14.	At the Installation Summary screen, configure the following
		•	Under Localization
		•		Keyboard
		•		Language Support
		•		Time and Date
 		•	Under System
		•		Installation Destination 
		•		Under Local Standard Disks
		•		Select AMD-RAID Array
		•	Under Storage Configuration
		•		Select Custom			
		•	In the upper-left corner, click Done
		•	Click the Click here to create them automatically link
			Note: AMD-RAID only supports a file system type of ext4, using the XFS file system will cause an unrecoverable installation error.	
		•	Under Installation
				Select Data /home
				Change file system to ext4
				Select system /boot
				Change file system to ext4
				Select system /rhel-root
				Change file system to ext4
			In the upper left corner, Click Done
			In the Summary of Changes window, Click Accept Changes
		•	Network and Hostname
		•		In the bottom left corner, enter a valid Hostname
		•		Select an Ethernet Port
		•		In the bottom right corner,  Click Configure
		•		Enter valid entries
		•		Click Save
		•		Under Ethernet, click th ON button
		•		In the upper left corner, Click Done
	15. 	Under Software
		•	Connect to Red Hat
		•	Enter a valid User name
		•	Enter a valid Password
		•	Click Register
		•	In the upper-left corner, click Done
		Installation Source
		•	Software Selection
		•		Select Server with GUI
		•	In the upper left corner, Click Done
	16.	Under User Settings:
		•	Click Root Password
		•		Enter an applicable root password
		•		Re-enter the root password
		•	Click User Creation
		•		Enter a Full Name
		•		Enter a Username
		•		Enter an applicable password
		•		Re-enter the user password
		•	In the upper right corner, Click Done
	17.	In the bottom right corner, Click  Beginning Installation
	NOTE: system may appear to be locked up, please wait patiently, the system is busy writing out files and will respond shortly.

	18.	At the Installation Complete
		•	In the bottom right corner, Click Reboot
		•	Once the installation media has been ejected, remove it
	19.	At the Initial Setup Window
		•	Click License Information
		•	Review and Select (Check Mark) I accept the License Agreement
		•	In the upper left corner, Click Done
		•	If not already done, configure Network and Host name
		•	In the bottom right corner, Click Finish Configuration 
	20.	Login to the system
		•	Select a user
		•	Enter a password
	21.	At the Welcome window
		•	Select the desired Language
		•	Click Next
	22.	At the Typing Window
		•	Select the desired keyboard layout
		•	Click Next
	23.	If desired, Configure Privacy
		•	Click Next
		•	Click Deny Access or Grant Access to give Color access to your location?
		•	If desired, Configure Connect your Online Accounts
		•	Click Next  or Skip
	24.	Click Start using Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server

